    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      404.44,
      391.42,
      419.98
    ],
    "text": "Inmate Suicide at Jaffna Prison - JAFFNA POLICE",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      434.46,
      526.41,
      517.08
    ],
    "text": "Investigations have been launched following a report received by the Jaffna Police regarding a high-profile inmate. The deceased, a 46-year-old resident of Pungudutivu, had been convicted and sentenced to capital punishment by the Jaffna High Court for his involvement in the 2015 murder of a schoolgirl within the Kayts Police Division. The individual reportedly committed suicide by hanging inside the Jaffna Prison premises on the morning of May 25, 2026.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0,
      13.5600004196167
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      531.3,
      526.29,
      599.81
    ],
    "text": "The deceased was one of four convicts sentenced to death for the murder who had subsequently filed an appeal challenging the initial verdict. The appellate judgment was scheduled to be delivered today, May 25, 2026. Preliminary inquiries reveal that the inmate hanged himself after being transferred from the Welikada Prison to the Jaffna Prison on May 24, 2026, ahead of his scheduled appearance before the Honorable High Court of Jaffna.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      614.25,
      526.21,
      655.13
    ],
    "text": "Following a formal Magistrate\u2019s inquest, the body has been transferred to the Jaffna Hospital morgue for a post-mortem examination. Advanced investigations into the incident are currently being spearheaded by the Jaffna Police Station.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
